ader":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/BooleanRing.html#BooleanRing.toBooleanAlgebra\"><span class=\"name\">BooleanRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">toBooleanAlgebra</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/BooleanRing.html#BooleanRing\">BooleanRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/BooleanAlgebra/Defs.html#BooleanAlgebra\">BooleanAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Boolean algebra structure on a Boolean ring.\n\nThe data is defined so that:\n* `a ⊔ b` unfolds to `a + b + a * b`\n* `a ⊓ b` unfolds to `a * b`\n* `a ≤ b` unfolds to `a + b + a * b = b`\n* `⊥` unfolds to `0`\n* `⊤` unfolds to `1`\n* `aᶜ` unfolds to `1 + a`\n* `a \\ b` unfolds to `a * (1 + b)`\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/BooleanRing.html#BooleanRing.toBooleanAlgebra","kind":"def","line":208,"name":"BooleanRing.toBooleanAlgebra","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/BooleanRing.lean#L208-L236"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/BooleanRing.html#BooleanRing.le_sup_inf\"><span class=\"name\">BooleanRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">le_sup_inf</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\